<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="16.[189,303,966,992]" box="[189,303,966,992]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,303,966,992]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,303,966,992]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[189,1399,1019,1339]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<taxonomicName authority="Grootaert &amp; Shamshev, 2012" authorityName="Grootaert &amp; Shamshev" authorityYear="2012" box="[189,503,1019,1045]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Platypalpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="singaporensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[189,503,1019,1045]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Platypalpus singaporensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[516,611,1020,1046]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
belongs to the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Meigen" baseAuthorityYear="1804" box="[810,914,1019,1045]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Platypalpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luteus">
<emphasis box="[810,914,1019,1045]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">P. luteus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group as indicated by the long yellow proboscis and many other features (
<bibRefCitation author="Grootaert &amp; Shamshev" box="[624,978,1061,1088]" firstAuthor="Grootaert" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" pagination="4031 - 4065" refId="ref69126" refString="Grootaert P. &amp; Shamshev I. 2006. The genus Platypalpus Macquart (Diptera: Hybotidae) from Northeast Thailand with comments on the species groups in the Oriental region. Journal of Natural History 39 (47): 4031 - 4065. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222930500533781" type="journal article" year="2006">Grootaert &amp; Shamshev 2006</bibRefCitation>
). It is however aberrant because it lacks the broadened fore tarsi like other members of the group. 
<taxonomicName authority="Grootaert &amp; Shamshev, 2012" authorityName="Grootaert &amp; Shamshev" authorityYear="2012" box="[979,1293,1103,1129]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Platypalpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="singaporensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[979,1293,1103,1129]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Platypalpus singaporensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1304,1399,1103,1129]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
has to be compared mainly with 
<taxonomicName authority="Grootaert &amp; Shamshev" authorityName="Grootaert &amp; Shamshev" authorityYear="2006" box="[579,1002,1144,1171]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Platypalpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hualuang">
<emphasis box="[579,720,1145,1171]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">P. hualuang</emphasis>
Grootaert &amp; Shamshev
</taxonomicName>
, a similar species from Northeast 
<collectingCountry box="[189,297,1186,1212]" name="Thailand" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Thailand</collectingCountry>
. There are however so many crucial differences that show the plasticity of the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Meigen" baseAuthorityYear="1804" box="[1217,1315,1186,1212]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Platypalpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luteus">
<emphasis box="[1217,1315,1186,1212]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">P. luteus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group. Remarkable is the presence in 
<taxonomicName authority="Grootaert &amp; Shamshev, 2012" authorityName="Grootaert &amp; Shamshev" authorityYear="2012" box="[544,734,1229,1254]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Platypalpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="singaporensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[544,734,1229,1254]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">P. singaporensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[741,831,1229,1255]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
of a row of about 8 setae along the upper margin of the anepisternum. A feature that is unique in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Macquart" authorityYear="1827" box="[750,890,1270,1296]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Platypalpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[750,890,1270,1296]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Platypalpus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Grootaert &amp; Shamshev" authorityYear="2006" box="[1058,1198,1270,1296]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Platypalpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hualuang">
<emphasis box="[1058,1198,1270,1296]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">P. hualuang</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
one or two short yellowish setae are present, a character that we overlooked in the original description of this species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[189,1399,1384,1662]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
In 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Grootaert &amp; Shamshev" authorityYear="2006" box="[224,366,1384,1410]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Platypalpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hualuang">
<emphasis box="[224,366,1384,1410]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">P. hualuang</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the following characters are different: antenna onion-shaped (
<figureCitation box="[1126,1217,1384,1410]" captionStart="Figs 19-26" captionStartId="10.[189,241,1895,1921]" captionTargetBox="[218,1297,308,1855]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[218,1369,265,1855]" captionText="Figs 19-26. Antennae of Tachydromiinae. 19. Platypalpus singaporensis sp. nov. 20. Platypalpus hualuang Grootaert &amp; Shamshev, 2006. 21. Tachydromia luang Shamshev &amp; Grootaert, 2005. 22. Drapetis mandai sp. nov. 23. Drapetis hutan sp. nov. 24. Chersodromia singaporensis Shamshev &amp; Grootaert, 2005. 25. Crossopalpus temasek sp. nov. 26. Stilpon singaporensis sp. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3715179" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3715179/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Fig. 20</figureCitation>
), palpus small, round, pale yellow; a pair of short pale yellow ocellar bristles; two pairs of short, pale verticals; 1 notopleural; a brown median band on mesonotum; fore tibia not swollen in basal half and without black dorsal bristles; tarsi paler than tibiae, almost white; fore tarsus very long, longer than tibia; fore tarsomere 1 with a long white bristle near base; fore tarsomere 3 and 4 flattened and widened, due to a wing-like posterior protuberance; mid femur with about 6 posteroventral bristles about half as long as femur is wide; mid tarsus long, as long as mid tibia.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[189,1399,1707,2026]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<taxonomicName authority="Grootaert &amp; Shamshev, 2012" authorityName="Grootaert &amp; Shamshev" authorityYear="2012" box="[189,505,1707,1733]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Platypalpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="singaporensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[189,505,1707,1733]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Platypalpus singaporensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[518,615,1708,1734]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Grootaert &amp; Shamshev" authorityYear="2006" box="[788,934,1707,1733]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Platypalpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hualuang">
<emphasis box="[788,934,1707,1733]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">P. hualuang</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as follows: antenna ellipsoid; palpus elongate, brown; a pair of long black ocellar bristles; two pairs of long black verticals; a narrow brown vitta on each row of dorsocentrals, median area of mesonotum yellow; 2 notopleurals; fore tibia swollen in basal half and dorsally with some long black bristles; fore tarsus distinctly shorter than fore tibia; all tarsi yellow, not paler than tibiae; fore tarsomere 1 without long basal pale ventral bristle, only with longer ventral pubescence; fore tarsomeres 3, 4 and 5 flattened, but not widened; mid femur with a row of 8-10 brown posteroventral bristles that are at least 3/4 as long as femur is wide; mid tarsus short, about 3/4 length of mid tibia.
</paragraph>
